         <abstract id="aspace_ebc595da0733674eee4b2f7fd1d3e51c">The Elizabeth Montagu Collection contains letters to and from her friends and relatives. Family highlights include twenty letters Montagu wrote to her husband Edward, ten letters to and from her sister Sarah Robinson Scott, and one from her brother brother, Matthew Robinson-Morris, Baron Rokeby, who wrote his opinion of their cousin Elizabeth Lumley marrying the author Laurence Sterne, whom he described as "a Parson, who once delighted in debauchery." Also present are communications to and from Montagu's bluestocking friends including Anne Donnellan, Margaret Cavendish-Harley, Duchess of Portland, Ann Dillingham Ord, Benjamin Stillingfleet, and Elizabeth Vesey, as well as family friends Rev. William Freind and Dr. John Gilbert. The outlying correspondence is three letters from 1909 written by Montagu's editor Emily J. Climenson; they came with the collection and provide provenance documentation.</abstract>
